The paper discusses an experiment on ad-auction, which is a classic topic in game theory and mechanism design (cs.GT). The paper evaluates a recent approach to econometrics based on regret minimization (cs.EC), which is a subfield of game theory and optimization. The paper also discusses the role of human behavior in the ad-auction experiment, which involves decision-making and learning (cs.AI). The paper uses statistical methods to analyze the data and estimate values, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper suggests ways to improve the accuracy of the estimated values, which involves optimization and algorithm design (cs.SI).
